There are 3 cricket grounds. {Scalby's}has a modern pavilion with public bar. {Burniston's}is combined with a football pitch. {Scarborough cricket club was founded in 1849 and its present ground in{North Marine {Road}dates from 1863. Town, county and international matches are played here. Its annual September Cricket Festival attracts teams from all over the world. The ground accomodates up to 12,000 spectators.
Scarborough's Rugby Union Football Club has a ground and club house at {Newby}open to the public and a practice field at{Silver Royd.}
{ Scalby beck}provides both public and private fishing.
